The paper discusses the interference-to-noise ratio (INR) in millimeter-wave cellular networks, which is a topic related to network information theory (cs.IT) and network communication (cs.COM). The paper also uses statistical channel models to assess the INR, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the effects of antenna array size and patterns, which are topics related to wireless networking (cs.NI) and millimeter-wave communication (cs.MM).
